reviews.review_text:
Special Franklins One of my favorite versions of Franklin's with Jerry and Brent extending gleeful licks towards one and other.

A standout show for playing and performance.

Charlie's transfer is clean and perfect.

A no-debate-about-it five star show

I Can Imagine I can imagine being late for this show, entering the venue right when they start playing Feel Like a Stranger and thinking this is a Hot opener. Anyway, showcased here are some of the new tunes Brough forth from the Fall '82; Dupree's, Touch & Thrown Stones. "Like running a red light"

40 yrs today Had the pleasure to enjoy this show again
The Franklins is a tower and the bell was rung
